KVM SR-IOV VMM and VNM Driver
version 0.2

Scripted Install

A basic install script is provided with this driver. To install the driver
execute "install" as root and follow the on screen instructions

Manual Install

1. Copy the "vmm" directory to your "remotes/vmm" directory
2. Replace the contents of "remotes/vnm/ovswitch" with the contents of the 
   "vnm" directory
3. Edit the "remotes/vmm/<driver>/kvmrc" file to suit your environment
4. Specify the available virtual functions in "remotes/vmm/<driver>/vf_maps/<file>"
5. Specify the device and port mappings in "remotes/vmm/<driver>/vf_maps/<file>_ofed"
6. Execute "onehost sync"

Detailed install instructions can be found here:
http://wiki.chpc.ac.za/acelab:opennebula_sr-iov_vmm_driver
